premise_source_doc_sentence: With an estimated height of , it is considerably taller than any other known Neanderthal , and its skull has by far the largest cranial capacity  (  1736-1740 cm3  )  of any archaic hominin skull ever found , making it , according to Ralph Holloway , one of the most famous specimens of Neanderthal skulls .
